 :tx/rationale "Create task: LIVESTORE-5: Systematic migration of all commands to LiveStore. CONTEXT: After LIVESTORE-4 validates the pattern on status.rs, migrate the remaining ~25 commands (120+ call sites across 30+ files). The migration is mechanical: replace DiskLayout::open + load_store with LiveStore::open, replace layout.write_tx with live.write_tx, replace &store with live.store(). APPROACH: (1) Create LiveStore at the top-level command dispatch in mod.rs/main.rs. Pass &mut LiveStore to each command's run() function. (2) Commands that only READ (query, log, schema, seed, analyze without --commit) can take &LiveStore (immutable). (3) Commands that WRITE (observe, task create/close/update, harvest, spec create, bilateral --commit, witness, trace --commit, config set, challenge) take &mut LiveStore. (4) The MCP server (mcp.rs) is the most complex migration: it has 18 call sites and runs as a long-lived process. It should create ONE LiveStore at startup and share it across all tool invocations — this is essentially the daemon pattern. (5) main.rs session auto-detect (ST-1) and RFL-2 feedback currently create their own DiskLayout + load_store. These become LiveStore::open() at process start, reused by the command dispatch. (6) For commands that currently reload the store after writing (e.g., harvest.rs line 899: load_store after write_tx), the reload becomes unnecessary — LiveStore already has the updated state. Remove the redundant load_store calls. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Zero calls to DiskLayout::open + load_store in any command's run() function (they all receive LiveStore). (B) Zero calls to layout.write_tx() (replaced with live.write_tx()). (C) DiskLayout::open and load_store still exist for backward compat and for LiveStore::open() itself. (D) All 1736+ tests pass. (E) Every command produces identical output to pre-migration. DEPENDS-ON: LIVESTORE-4 (pattern validated). FILE: all files in crates/braid/src/commands/ + crates/braid/src/mcp.rs + crates/braid/src/main.rs"
